<dl id="n53122k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53122k">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53122k"> 122(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Asita (Simeon) <small>Not cancelled</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53122k"><li>FW 60.16 </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/lexc.htm#n53122k">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/l39c.htm#n53122k">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53122k">MS BL 47476b-177</ms> </li><li>JJA 49:375 <a name="cd10" href="../../ff/fdra/cda.htm#cd10">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/c/cd10.htm#n53122k">Draft: I.3&sect;1.10</a>/2.10/3.10</li> </ul> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53122k"></li><li>FW 110.08 </li><li><a href="../../flex/e/lexe.htm#n53122k">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/e/l39e.htm#n53122k">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53122k">MS BL 47476a-209</ms> </li><li>JJA 49:441 <a name="ed11" href="../../ff/fdra/eda.htm#ed11">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/e/ed11.htm#n53122k">Draft: I.5&sect;1.11</a>/4.11</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Or, par la vertu de son aust&eacute;rit&eacute;, <mark>Asita</mark>, le grand asc&egrave;te, connut la naissance de celui qui plus tard sauverait les cr&eacute;atures de la douleur de rena&icirc;tre. Et, comme il avait soif de la bonne loi, il arriva dans la demeure du roi &Ccedil;ouddhodana. Il alla, d&apos;un pas ferme tout pr&egrave;s de l&apos;appartement des femmes. Il avait l&apos;autorit&eacute; grave de la science et celle de la vieillesse. <small> A. Ferdinand Herold, <a name="AFHB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#AFHB"><cite title="source">La Vie Du Bouddha</cite></a> (1922) 18</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: After the infant was born, the aged hermit Asita came to the place to see him, and when the sage had examined the marks of divinity on the infant&apos;s body, he proclaimed that the one who was the destroy the evil of rebirth. Asita corresponds to Saint Simeon in Luke 2.25-32. </mm> </dd></dl>
